Deputy President William Ruto on Saturday send his condolences to the family of Anthony Kariuki, who was one of his staff members. Ruto described Kariuki as a person who was sharp, dependable, industrious, committed and creative with a positive attitude. He added that the staff will miss Kariuki's punctuality, team spirit and his orientation to detail. Kariuki worked for Nation Media Group as a digital editor before he joined DP Ruto as social media director. Kariuki died after he was hit by a motorists in Esatlands.